article_title: Natural Gas Sinks to Three-Year Low
article_text:
NEW YORK--Natural gas futures fell to fresh three-year lows Thursday as expectations of continued weak demand outweighed a smaller-than-expected inventory build.

Futures for November delivery settled down 1.8 cents, or 0.7%, at $2.386 a million British thermal units on the New York Mercantile Exchange, the lowest settlement since June 13, 2012.

Natural gas inventories typically rise at this time of year as producers stock up...
